The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the National Summit of Crime Reduction and Public Safety. Pence praises Attorney General Jeff Sessions for his leadership and discusses President Donald Trump's commitment to supporting law enforcement and ensuring the safety of American citizens. Pence highlights the efforts of the administration to reduce crime, strengthen law enforcement, and secure the borders. He also emphasizes the need for collaboration between different levels of law enforcement and community groups. Pence concludes by expressing his gratitude to law enforcement officers and promising to provide them with the resources and respect they deserve.